EPT ChampionshipIEM COLOGNE 2024

The bells toll and the Cathedral of Counter-Strike is looking to crown a new champion! In 2024, IEM Cologne returns to the Lanxess Arena where 24 of the world’s best teams will compete for a $1M prize pool, an Intel Grand Slam contribution and the second EPT Championship title of the year. Get your tickets and become part of an unforgettable experience alongside thousands of other passionate fans. For all we know, history will be made but who will prove themselves as the true kings of Counter-Strike?

Tickets for IEM Cologne 2024 are live! Wave 1 ended on the 2nd of November and all premium tickets for the event have now been sold out. Wave 3 tickets are currently live, offering both 1-day and 3-day options. So pick up yours while you can and come to experience the legendary Cathedral of Counter-Strike!

Format and Teams

Stage 1

  • 16 Team Double-Elimination bracket
  • All matches Bo3
  • Top 8 Teams advanced to Group Stage

Stage 2

  • 2 x 8 Team Double-Elimination brackets
  • All matches Bo3
  • Top 3 of each group advance to Playoffs
  • Group stage winners advance to Semifinals
  • Group stage runners-up advance to Quarterfinals as the High Seeds
  • Group stage 3rd place teams advance to Quarterfinals as the Low Seeds
PlayOffs
  • 6 Team Single-Elimination bracket
  • Quarterfinals & Semifinals Bo3
  • Grand Final Bo5

THIS IS IEM COLOGNE

Culminating in the heart of Cologne, the Cathedral of Counter-Strike has become a temple for history making. The event's significance lies in its long-lasting traditions and ability to consistently deliver iconic and memorable moments. With determination to run every year since 2014, IEM Cologne has been the hallowed ground for three CS:GO Majors, bringing together the greatest players and thousands of passionate fans to share and celebrate their love for the game.

The Lanxess Arena has become a venue well known for its roaring crowds and electrifying atmosphere. Up to this day, IEM Cologne remains a beloved event, serving as a showcase of the game's longevity, enduring competitive spirit and the ever evolving world of eSports.

FAQs

Is this tournament played on Counter-Strike 2?

Yes, the 2024 event will be the first IEM Cologne played on Counter-Strike 2!

Is there an age restriction for the event?

Please note that the minimum age to attend this event is 16.
It is not possible to attend the event if you are below the age of 16. 

Do you have additional accessibility information available?

You can find additional accessibility information on the website of the Lanxess Arena: https://www.lanxess-arena.de/besucherinfos/barrierefreiheit 

Q: Can I bring my plus 1 for free?  

A: ESL provides free tickets for your plus 1, when you are not able to attend the event without a person who takes care of you/accompanies you. 

Examples: When you are (partially) deaf and need to bring your own interpreter with you; or when you need a person to assist you with your medical devices, wheelchair, etc. Please contact us via ticketing@eslgaming.com to request plus 1 extra ticket please.

Can I get a refund for my ticket?

No, tickets are non-refundable.

Is it safe to buy a ticket from the secondary market?

Buying tickets from the secondary market is now possible via TicketSwap. TicketSwap is a platform where you can safely resell & buy tickets from other fans. If you are no longer able to attend the event and want to sell your ticket or want to check out last minute ticket opportunities, please visit TicketSwap.

We strongly advise you to only use our shop or TicketSwap for any ticket purchases. We cannot guarantee that a ticket you bought from other third parties will be valid for this event.

Can I get food at the venue?

Yes, there will be a variety of food & beverage options available in the arena.

What can I bring into the venue?

Please only bring small personal belongings. Anything larger than an A4 document will not be allowed.

It is explictly not allowed to bring:

  • Weapons of all kinds
  • Sharp objects like umbrellas 
  • Drugs
  • Pyrotechnics
  • Food
  • Drinks
  • Bottles
  • Animals
  • Professional cameras
Can I bring instruments or flags & banners?

We appreciate that fans want to create an unforgettable atmosphere in the venue.
However, if you want to bring any instrument, flag or banner, please contact us via ticketing@eslgaming.com so we can register you for the event. Otherwise, you will not be allowed. to bring any of these items into the arena.

What is the schedule for the event?

The exact event schedule might be a work in progress at this point.

The schedule will likely be roughly similar to the 2023 event. In 2023, we had the following opening hours:

  • Friday: Outdoor Area 11AM
  • Saturday: Outdoor Area 12:30PM
  • Sunday: Outdoor Area 12:30PM

Located prominently within Qiddiya City, the Gaming & Esports District will be home to multiple dedicated esports venues — one of which will be among the top three largest in the world — plus next-gen facilities that will host up to 19 top-tier esports clubs at once, each with dedicated facilities like scrim rooms and strategy theater – and the regional headquarters of leading video game companies. About Molkerei Alois Müller GmbH & Co. KG Founded in 1896 by Ludwig Müller, the former village dairy developed into a modern large dairy from the time it was taken over by Theo Müller in 1971. Around 140 million kg of milk are now processed into high-quality dairy products at the Alois Müller dairy's Swabian headquarters. In many product groups, Müller has created a market with numerous innovations in the first place. For example, buttermilk, kefir, Müller Corner, Müller Rice or the flavoured Müllermilch. The company still holds top positions in these segments. The Müller brand is almost 100 percent well known and practically everyone in Germany knows the slogan: "Alles Müller, oder was?"
